            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> @echasnovski does this enable any features/simplifications to `vim._with` ?\r\n\r\nJudging only by the word descriptions, I don't think so. The `vim._with` function [already could return multiple values](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/45e63ee3a85a18ab04e8ee8c23c7239ec141072a/runtime/lua/vim/_core/shared.lua#L1651-L1656) ([here is a test](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/45e63ee3a85a18ab04e8ee8c23c7239ec141072a/test/functional/lua/with_spec.lua#L1443-L1456), although it doesn't explicitly test for window context) with a different window as a context:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal w, h = vim._with({ win = win_id }, function() return vim.api.nvim_win_get_width(0), vim.api.nvim_win_get_height(0) end)\r\n```",
